title: Lordz.Of.Brooklyn.All.In.The.Family.FLAC
description:
Lordz Of Brooklyn (short L.O.B.) now known as The Lordz are a American crossover Hip hop/Rock group composed of brothers and childhood friends of mostly Irish American and Italian American descent from Brooklyn, New York. The original line up consisted of the McLeer brothers, Ad Money (aka DJ ADM) and (Mr.) Kaves, with Scotty Edge, Dino Bottz and Paulie Nugent (aka Paulie 2Times).
Throughout their career, the Lordz Of Brooklyn have collaborated with many artists, including Everlast, Liroy, Busta Rhymes ("Forget Bout It Bout It"), Ozzy Osbourne (Busta Rhyme's "Iron Man" cover), Tim Armstrong ("Outlaw"), KoRn ("White Trash" remix), Shanti ("Momma's Boy" new version), Danny Diablo ("PSK What Does It Mean" Schooly D cover) and others.
